  "prompt": "I am doing 3rd integrated MS.c.Life sciences and I am going to apply for INSA summer research fellowship.What the write up should contain generally?",
  "response": "For the INSA (Indian National Science Academy) Summer Research Fellowship write-up, you should generally include the following components:\n\n1. Personal Information\n- Name\n- Institution\n- Course and semester\n- Contact details\n\n2. Academic Background\n- Academic performance\n- Relevant coursework\n- CGPA/percentage\n- Academic achievements\n\n3. Research Interest\n- Specific area of research\n- Your motivation\n- Previous research experience (if any)\n- Research objectives\n\n4. Fellowship Objectives\n- Why you want to pursue this fellowship\n- How it aligns with your academic/research goals\n- Expected learning outcomes\n\n5. Research Proposal\n- Brief research problem/topic\n- Methodology\n- Potential impact\n- Timeline\n\n6. Key Components to Highlight\n- Scientific curiosity\n- Potential contribution\n- Interdisciplinary approach\n- Innovation\n\n7. Supporting Documents\n- Academic transcripts\n- Recommendation letters\n- Research abstracts\n- Publications (if any)\n\nAdditional Tips:\n- Be concise (2-3 pages)\n- Use clear, professional language\n- Demonstrate passion for research\n- Proofread thoroughly\n- Align with INSA fellowship guidelines\n\nRemember to customize your write-up to showcase your unique strengths and research potential.",
